Fire attack on Turkish travel agency in Zurich 
Fire damaged a Turkish travel agency in Zurich in an arson attack
blamed by Swiss police Thursday on members of the separatist Kurdish
Workers' Party (PKK).
The attack was the latest in a series against Turkish interests in
several Swiss cities and towns over the past month.
The latest happened several men threw firebombs through the agency
window overnight Wednesday. Firemen quickly brought the blaze under
control.
Kurdish sympathisers demonstrated at the United Nations headquarters in
Geneva on Tuesday to protest the UN's "silence" over Turkey's military
offensive in northern Iraq against what Ankara alleges are PKK bases.
Four UN security guards and three Swiss policemen were injured, one
seriously, in clashes which erupted during the demonstration. Two
demonstrators were arrested.
